<p style="text-align: left;page-break-after:auto" class="MsoNormal"><a name="_8462eb40-f4ec-a98b-eb74-929f0dd762cb" id="_8462eb40-f4ec-a98b-eb74-929f0dd762cb"></a><u>Remarks:</u></p>

<div class="ul_wrap" style="page-break-after:auto"><p style="mso-list:l3 level1 lfo5;page-break-after:auto" class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst"><a name="_e0b27521-f462-d038-d5e6-d66be185f3c6" id="_e0b27521-f462-d038-d5e6-d66be185f3c6"></a>The purpose of having separate attributes for <i>agencyName</i> and  <i>agencyResponsibleForProduction</i> is to distinguish between the organization responsible for the S-128 dataset&#x2019;s content (<i>agencyResponsibleForProduction</i>) and the organization that actually carries out the production process (<i>agencyName</i>). This separation allow flexibility in cases where the producing agency acts on behalf of another responsible body, ensuring that both roles are clearly identified.
</p>
</div>

